213static void networkStateChanged(bool isOnLine)
214{
215 Vector<Ref<Frame>> frames;
216
217 // Get all the frames of all the pages in all the page groups
218 for (auto* page : allPages()) {
219 for (Frame* frame = &page->mainFrame(); frame; frame = frame->tree().traverseNext())
220 frames.append(*frame);
221 InspectorInstrumentation::networkStateChanged(*page);
222 }
223
224 auto& eventName = isOnLine ? eventNames().onlineEvent : eventNames().offlineEvent;
225 for (auto& frame : frames) {
226 if (!frame->document())
227 continue;
228 frame->document()->dispatchWindowEvent(Event::create(eventName, Event::CanBubble::No, Event::IsCancelable::No));
229 }
230}

294 , m_performanceMonitor(isUtilityPage() ? nullptr : makeUnique<PerformanceMonitor>(*this))
295 , m_lowPowerModeNotifier(makeUnique<LowPowerModeNotifier>([this](bool isLowPowerModeEnabled) { handleLowModePowerChange(isLowPowerModeEnabled); }))
296 , m_performanceLogging(makeUnique<PerformanceLogging>(*this))
297#if PLATFORM(MAC) && (ENABLE(SERVICE_CONTROLS) || ENABLE(TELEPHONE_NUMBER_DETECTION))
298 , m_servicesOverlayController(makeUnique<ServicesOverlayController>(*this))
299#endif
300 , m_imageOverlayController(makeUnique<ImageOverlayController>(*this))
301 , m_recentWheelEventDeltaFilter(WheelEventDeltaFilter::create())
302 , m_pageOverlayController(makeUnique<PageOverlayController>(*this))
303#if ENABLE(APPLE_PAY)
304 , m_paymentCoordinator(makeUnique<PaymentCoordinator>(*pageConfiguration.paymentCoordinatorClient))
305#endif
306#if ENABLE(WEB_AUTHN)
307 , m_authenticatorCoordinator(makeUniqueRef<AuthenticatorCoordinator>(WTFMove(pageConfiguration.authenticatorCoordinatorClient)))
308#endif
309#if ENABLE(APPLICATION_MANIFEST)
310 , m_applicationManifest(pageConfiguration.applicationManifest)
311#endif
312#if ENABLE(DEVICE_ORIENTATION) && PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
313 , m_deviceOrientationUpdateProvider(WTFMove(pageConfiguration.deviceOrientationUpdateProvider))
314#endif
315 , m_corsDisablingPatterns(WTFMove(pageConfiguration.corsDisablingPatterns))
316 , m_allowedNetworkHosts(WTFMove(pageConfiguration.allowedNetworkHosts))
317 , m_loadsSubresources(pageConfiguration.loadsSubresources)
318 , m_shouldRelaxThirdPartyCookieBlocking(pageConfiguration.shouldRelaxThirdPartyCookieBlocking)
319 , m_httpsUpgradeEnabled(pageConfiguration.httpsUpgradeEnabled)
320{
321 updateTimerThrottlingState();
322
323 m_pluginInfoProvider->addPage(*this);
324 m_userContentProvider->addPage(*this);
325 m_visitedLinkStore->addPage(*this);
326
327 static bool addedListener;
328 if (!addedListener) {
329 platformStrategies()->loaderStrategy()->addOnlineStateChangeListener(&networkStateChanged);
330 addedListener = true;
331 }
332
333 ASSERT(!allPages().contains(this));
334 allPages().add(this);
335
336 if (!isUtilityPage()) {
337 ++nonUtilityPageCount;
338 MemoryPressureHandler::setPageCount(nonUtilityPageCount);
339 }
340
341#ifndef NDEBUG
342 pageCounter.increment();
343#endif
344
345#if ENABLE(REMOTE_INSPECTOR)
346 if (m_inspectorController->inspectorClient() && m_inspectorController->inspectorClient()->allowRemoteInspectionToPageDirectly())
347 m_inspectorDebuggable->init();
348#endif
349
350#if PLATFORM(COCOA)
351 platformInitialize();
352#endif
353
354#if USE(LIBWEBRTC)
355 m_libWebRTCProvider->setH265Support(RuntimeEnabledFeatures::sharedFeatures().webRTCH265CodecEnabled());
356 m_libWebRTCProvider->setVP9Support(RuntimeEnabledFeatures::sharedFeatures().webRTCVP9Profile0CodecEnabled(), RuntimeEnabledFeatures::sharedFeatures().webRTCVP9Profile2CodecEnabled());
357#endif
358
359 if (!pageConfiguration.userScriptsShouldWaitUntilNotification)
360 m_hasBeenNotifiedToInjectUserScripts = true;
361
362 if (m_lowPowerModeNotifier->isLowPowerModeEnabled())
363 m_throttlingReasons.add(ThrottlingReason::LowPowerMode);
364}
365
366Page::~Page()
367{
368 ASSERT(!m_nestedRunLoopCount);
369 ASSERT(!m_unnestCallback);
370
371 m_validationMessageClient = nullptr;
372 m_diagnosticLoggingClient = nullptr;
373 m_performanceLoggingClient = nullptr;
374 m_mainFrame->setView(nullptr);
375 setGroupName(String());
376 allPages().remove(this);
377 if (!isUtilityPage()) {
378 --nonUtilityPageCount;
379 MemoryPressureHandler::setPageCount(nonUtilityPageCount);
380 }
381
382 m_settings->pageDestroyed();
383
384 m_inspectorController->inspectedPageDestroyed();
385
386 for (Frame* frame = &mainFrame(); frame; frame = frame->tree().traverseNext()) {
387 frame->willDetachPage();
388 frame->detachFromPage();
389 }
390
391 if (m_scrollingCoordinator)
392 m_scrollingCoordinator->pageDestroyed();
393
394 backForward().close();
395 if (!isUtilityPage())
396 BackForwardCache::singleton().removeAllItemsForPage(*this);
397
398#ifndef NDEBUG
399 pageCounter.decrement();
400#endif
401
402 m_pluginInfoProvider->removePage(*this);
403 m_userContentProvider->removePage(*this);
404 m_visitedLinkStore->removePage(*this);
405}

407void Page::clearPreviousItemFromAllPages(HistoryItem* item)
408{
409 for (auto* page : allPages()) {
410 auto& controller = page->mainFrame().loader().history();
411 if (item == controller.previousItem()) {
412 controller.clearPreviousItem();
413 return;
414 }
415 }

452{

490Ref<DOMRectList> Page::nonFastScrollableRectsForTesting()
491{
492 if (Document* document = m_mainFrame->document()) {
493 document->updateLayout();
494#if ENABLE(IOS_TOUCH_EVENTS)
495 document->updateTouchEventRegions();
496#endif
497 }
498
499 Vector<IntRect> rects;
500 if (ScrollingCoordinator* scrollingCoordinator = this->scrollingCoordinator()) {
501 const EventTrackingRegions& eventTrackingRegions = scrollingCoordinator->absoluteEventTrackingRegions();
502 for (const auto& synchronousEventRegion : eventTrackingRegions.eventSpecificSynchronousDispatchRegions)
503 rects.appendVector(synchronousEventRegion.value.rects());
504 }
505
506 Vector<FloatQuad> quads(rects.size());
507 for (size_t i = 0; i < rects.size(); ++i)
508 quads[i] = FloatRect(rects[i]);
509
510 return DOMRectList::create(quads);
511}

513Ref<DOMRectList> Page::touchEventRectsForEventForTesting(const String& eventName)

566void Page::goToItem(HistoryItem& item, FrameLoadType type, ShouldTreatAsContinuingLoad shouldTreatAsContinuingLoad)
567{
568 // stopAllLoaders may end up running onload handlers, which could cause further history traversals that may lead to the passed in HistoryItem
569 // being deref()-ed. Make sure we can still use it with HistoryController::goToItem later.
570 Ref<HistoryItem> protector(item);
571
572 auto& frameLoader = m_mainFrame->loader();
573 if (frameLoader.history().shouldStopLoadingForHistoryItem(item))
574 m_mainFrame->loader().stopAllLoadersAndCheckCompleteness();
575
576 m_mainFrame->loader().history().goToItem(item, type, shouldTreatAsContinuingLoad);
577}
578
579void Page::setGroupName(const String& name)
580{
581 if (m_group && !m_group->name().isEmpty()) {
582 ASSERT(m_group != m_singlePageGroup.get());
583 ASSERT(!m_singlePageGroup);
584 m_group->removePage(*this);
585 }
586
587 if (name.isEmpty())
588 m_group = m_singlePageGroup.get();
589 else {
590 m_singlePageGroup = nullptr;
591 m_group = PageGroup::pageGroup(name);
592 m_group->addPage(*this);
593 }
594}

606 m_group = m_singlePageGroup.get();
607}

609void Page::updateStyleAfterChangeInEnvironment()
610{
611 forEachDocument([] (Document& document) {
612 if (auto* styleResolver = document.styleScope().resolverIfExists())
613 styleResolver->invalidateMatchedDeclarationsCache();
614 document.scheduleFullStyleRebuild();
615 document.styleScope().didChangeStyleSheetEnvironment();
616 document.scheduleRenderingUpdate(RenderingUpdateStep::MediaQueryEvaluation);
617 });
618}

621{
622 for (auto* page : allPages())
623 page->updateStyleAfterChangeInEnvironment();
624}

668inline std::optional<std::pair<MediaCanStartListener&, Document&>> Page::takeAnyMediaCanStartListener()
669{
670 for (Frame* frame = &mainFrame(); frame; frame = frame->tree().traverseNext()) {
671 if (!frame->document())
672 continue;
673 if (MediaCanStartListener* listener = frame->document()->takeAnyMediaCanStartListener())
674 return { { *listener, *frame->document() } };
675 }
676 return std::nullopt;
677}
678
679void Page::setCanStartMedia(bool canStartMedia)
680{
681 if (m_canStartMedia == canStartMedia)
682 return;
683
684 m_canStartMedia = canStartMedia;
685
686 while (m_canStartMedia) {
687 auto listener = takeAnyMediaCanStartListener();
688 if (!listener)
689 break;
690 listener->first.mediaCanStart(listener->second);
691 }
692}

694static Frame* incrementFrame(Frame* curr, bool forward, CanWrap canWrap, DidWrap* didWrap = nullptr)
695{
696 return forward
697 ? curr->tree().traverseNext(canWrap, didWrap)
698 : curr->tree().traversePrevious(canWrap, didWrap);
699}
700
701bool Page::findString(const String& target, FindOptions options, DidWrap* didWrap)
702{
703 if (target.isEmpty())
704 return false;
705
706 CanWrap canWrap = options.contains(WrapAround) ? CanWrap::Yes : CanWrap::No;
707 Frame* frame = &focusController().focusedOrMainFrame();
708 Frame* startFrame = frame;
709 do {
710 if (frame->editor().findString(target, (options - WrapAround) | StartInSelection)) {
711 if (frame != startFrame)
712 startFrame->selection().clear();
713 focusController().setFocusedFrame(frame);
714 return true;
715 }
716 frame = incrementFrame(frame, !options.contains(Backwards), canWrap, didWrap);
717 } while (frame && frame != startFrame);
718
719 // Search contents of startFrame, on the other side of the selection that we did earlier.
720 // We cheat a bit and just research with wrap on
721 if (canWrap == CanWrap::Yes && !startFrame->selection().isNone()) {
722 if (didWrap)
723 *didWrap = DidWrap::Yes;
724 bool found = startFrame->editor().findString(target, options | WrapAround | StartInSelection);
725 focusController().setFocusedFrame(frame);
726 return found;
727 }
728
729 return false;
730}
731
732auto Page::findTextMatches(const String& target, FindOptions options, unsigned limit) -> MatchingRanges
733{
734 MatchingRanges result;
735
736 Frame* frame = &mainFrame();
737 Frame* frameWithSelection = nullptr;
738 do {
739 frame->editor().countMatchesForText(target, { }, options, limit ? (limit - result.ranges.size()) : 0, true, &result.ranges);
740 if (frame->selection().isRange())
741 frameWithSelection = frame;
742 frame = incrementFrame(frame, true, CanWrap::No);
743 } while (frame);
744
745 if (result.ranges.isEmpty())
746 return result;
747
748 if (frameWithSelection) {
749 result.indexForSelection = NoMatchAfterUserSelection;
750 auto selectedRange = *frameWithSelection->selection().selection().firstRange();
751 if (options.contains(Backwards)) {
752 for (size_t i = result.ranges.size(); i > 0; --i) {
753 // FIXME: Seems like this should be is_gteq to correctly handle the same string found twice in a row.
754 if (is_gt(treeOrder<ComposedTree>(selectedRange.start, result.ranges[i - 1].end))) {
755 result.indexForSelection = i - 1;
756 break;
757 }
758 }
759 } else {
760 for (size_t i = 0, size = result.ranges.size(); i < size; ++i) {
761 // FIXME: Seems like this should be is_lteq to correctly handle the same string found twice in a row.
762 if (is_lt(treeOrder<ComposedTree>(selectedRange.end, result.ranges[i].start))) {
763 result.indexForSelection = i;
764 break;
765 }
766 }
767 }
768 } else {
769 if (options.contains(Backwards))
770 result.indexForSelection = result.ranges.size() - 1;
771 else
772 result.indexForSelection = 0;
773 }
774
775 return result;
776}
777
778std::optional<SimpleRange> Page::rangeOfString(const String& target, const std::optional<SimpleRange>& referenceRange, FindOptions options)
779{
780 if (target.isEmpty())
781 return std::nullopt;
782
783 if (referenceRange && referenceRange->start.document().page() != this)
784 return std::nullopt;
785
786 CanWrap canWrap = options.contains(WrapAround) ? CanWrap::Yes : CanWrap::No;
787 Frame* frame = referenceRange ? referenceRange->start.document().frame() : &mainFrame();
788 Frame* startFrame = frame;
789 do {
790 if (auto resultRange = frame->editor().rangeOfString(target, frame == startFrame ? referenceRange : std::nullopt, options - WrapAround))
791 return resultRange;
792 frame = incrementFrame(frame, !options.contains(Backwards), canWrap);
793 } while (frame && frame != startFrame);
794
795 // Search contents of startFrame, on the other side of the reference range that we did earlier.
796 // We cheat a bit and just search again with wrap on.
797 if (canWrap == CanWrap::Yes && referenceRange) {
798 if (auto resultRange = startFrame->editor().rangeOfString(target, *referenceRange, options | WrapAround | StartInSelection))
799 return resultRange;
800 }
801
802 return std::nullopt;
803}
804
805unsigned Page::findMatchesForText(const String& target, FindOptions options, unsigned maxMatchCount, ShouldHighlightMatches shouldHighlightMatches, ShouldMarkMatches shouldMarkMatches)
806{
807 if (target.isEmpty())
808 return 0;
809
810 unsigned matchCount = 0;
811
812 Frame* frame = &mainFrame();
813 do {
814 if (shouldMarkMatches == MarkMatches)
815 frame->editor().setMarkedTextMatchesAreHighlighted(shouldHighlightMatches == HighlightMatches);
816 matchCount += frame->editor().countMatchesForText(target, std::nullopt, options, maxMatchCount ? (maxMatchCount - matchCount) : 0, shouldMarkMatches == MarkMatches, nullptr);
817 frame = incrementFrame(frame, true, CanWrap::No);
818 } while (frame);
819
820 return matchCount;
821}
822
823unsigned Page::markAllMatchesForText(const String& target, FindOptions options, bool shouldHighlight, unsigned maxMatchCount)
824{
825 return findMatchesForText(target, options, maxMatchCount, shouldHighlight ? HighlightMatches : DoNotHighlightMatches, MarkMatches);
826}
827
828unsigned Page::countFindMatches(const String& target, FindOptions options, unsigned maxMatchCount)
829{
830 return findMatchesForText(target, options, maxMatchCount, DoNotHighlightMatches, DoNotMarkMatches);
831}
832
833struct FindReplacementRange {
834 RefPtr<ContainerNode> root;
835 CharacterRange range;
836};
837
838static void replaceRanges(Page& page, const Vector<FindReplacementRange>& ranges, const String& replacementText)
839{
840 HashMap<RefPtr<ContainerNode>, Vector<FindReplacementRange>> rangesByContainerNode;
841 for (auto& range : ranges) {
842 auto& rangeList = rangesByContainerNode.ensure(range.root, [] {
843 return Vector<FindReplacementRange> { };
844 }).iterator->value;
845
846 // Ensure that ranges are sorted by their end offsets, per editing container.
847 auto endOffsetForRange = range.range.location + range.range.length;
848 auto insertionIndex = rangeList.size();
849 for (auto iterator = rangeList.rbegin(); iterator != rangeList.rend(); ++iterator) {
850 auto endOffsetBeforeInsertionIndex = iterator->range.location + iterator->range.length;
851 if (endOffsetForRange >= endOffsetBeforeInsertionIndex)
852 break;
853 insertionIndex--;
854 }
855 rangeList.insert(insertionIndex, range);
856 }
857
858 HashMap<RefPtr<Frame>, unsigned> frameToTraversalIndexMap;
859 unsigned currentFrameTraversalIndex = 0;
860 for (Frame* frame = &page.mainFrame(); frame; frame = frame->tree().traverseNext())
861 frameToTraversalIndexMap.set(frame, currentFrameTraversalIndex++);
862
863 // Likewise, iterate backwards (in document and frame order) through editing containers that contain text matches,
864 // so that we're consistent with our backwards iteration behavior per editing container when replacing text.
865 auto containerNodesInOrderOfReplacement = copyToVector(rangesByContainerNode.keys());
866 std::sort(containerNodesInOrderOfReplacement.begin(), containerNodesInOrderOfReplacement.end(), [frameToTraversalIndexMap] (auto& firstNode, auto& secondNode) {
867 if (firstNode == secondNode)
868 return false;
869
870 auto firstFrame = makeRefPtr(firstNode->document().frame());
871 if (!firstFrame)
872 return true;
873
874 auto secondFrame = makeRefPtr(secondNode->document().frame());
875 if (!secondFrame)
876 return false;
877
878 if (firstFrame == secondFrame) {
879 // Must not use Node::compareDocumentPosition here because some editing roots are inside shadow roots.
880 return is_gt(treeOrder<ComposedTree>(*firstNode, *secondNode));
881 }
882
883 return frameToTraversalIndexMap.get(firstFrame) > frameToTraversalIndexMap.get(secondFrame);
884 });
885
886 for (auto& container : containerNodesInOrderOfReplacement) {
887 auto frame = makeRefPtr(container->document().frame());
888 if (!frame)
889 continue;
890
891 // Iterate backwards through ranges when replacing text, such that earlier text replacements don't clobber replacement ranges later on.
892 auto& ranges = rangesByContainerNode.find(container)->value;
893 for (auto iterator = ranges.rbegin(); iterator != ranges.rend(); ++iterator) {
894 auto range = resolveCharacterRange(makeRangeSelectingNodeContents(*container), iterator->range);
895 if (range.collapsed())
896 continue;
897
898 frame->selection().setSelectedRange(range, Affinity::Downstream, FrameSelection::ShouldCloseTyping::Yes);
899 frame->editor().replaceSelectionWithText(replacementText, Editor::SelectReplacement::Yes, Editor::SmartReplace::No, EditAction::InsertReplacement);
900 }
901 }
902}
903
904uint32_t Page::replaceRangesWithText(const Vector<SimpleRange>& rangesToReplace, const String& replacementText, bool /*selectionOnly*/)
905{
906 // FIXME: In the future, we should respect the `selectionOnly` flag by checking whether each range being replaced is contained within its frame's selection.
907
908 Vector<FindReplacementRange> replacementRanges;
909 replacementRanges.reserveInitialCapacity(rangesToReplace.size());
910
911 for (auto& range : rangesToReplace) {
912 auto highestRoot = makeRefPtr(highestEditableRoot(makeDeprecatedLegacyPosition(range.start)));
913 if (!highestRoot || highestRoot != highestEditableRoot(makeDeprecatedLegacyPosition(range.end)) || !highestRoot->document().frame())
914 continue;
915 auto scope = makeRangeSelectingNodeContents(*highestRoot);
916 replacementRanges.append({ WTFMove(highestRoot), characterRange(scope, range) });
917 }
918
919 replaceRanges(*this, replacementRanges, replacementText);
920 return rangesToReplace.size();
921}
922
923uint32_t Page::replaceSelectionWithText(const String& replacementText)
924{
925 auto frame = makeRef(focusController().focusedOrMainFrame());
926 auto selection = frame->selection().selection();
927 if (!selection.isContentEditable())
928 return 0;
929
930 auto editAction = selection.isRange() ? EditAction::InsertReplacement : EditAction::Insert;
931 frame->editor().replaceSelectionWithText(replacementText, Editor::SelectReplacement::Yes, Editor::SmartReplace::No, editAction);
932 return 1;
933}

966
967Vector<Ref<Element>> Page::editableElementsInRect(const FloatRect& searchRectInRootViewCoordinates) const
968{
969 auto frameView = makeRefPtr(mainFrame().view());
970 if (!frameView)
971 return { };
972
973 auto document = makeRefPtr(mainFrame().document());
974 if (!document)
975 return { };
976
977 constexpr OptionSet<HitTestRequest::Type> hitType { HitTestRequest::Type::ReadOnly, HitTestRequest::Type::Active, HitTestRequest::Type::CollectMultipleElements, HitTestRequest::Type::DisallowUserAgentShadowContent, HitTestRequest::Type::AllowVisibleChildFrameContentOnly };
978 LayoutRect searchRectInMainFrameCoordinates = frameView->rootViewToContents(roundedIntRect(searchRectInRootViewCoordinates));
979 HitTestResult hitTestResult { searchRectInMainFrameCoordinates };
980 if (!document->hitTest(hitType, hitTestResult))
981 return { };
982
983 auto rootEditableElement = [](Node& node) -> Element* {
984 if (is<HTMLTextFormControlElement>(node)) {
985 if (downcast<HTMLTextFormControlElement>(node).isInnerTextElementEditable())
986 return &downcast<Element>(node);
987 } else if (is<Element>(node) && node.hasEditableStyle())
988 return node.rootEditableElement();
989 return nullptr;
990 };
991
992 ListHashSet<Ref<Element>> rootEditableElements;
993 auto& nodeSet = hitTestResult.listBasedTestResult();
994 for (auto& node : nodeSet) {
995 if (auto* editableElement = rootEditableElement(node)) {
996 ASSERT(searchRectInRootViewCoordinates.inclusivelyIntersects(editableElement->clientRect()));
997 rootEditableElements.add(*editableElement);
998 }
999 }
1000
1001 // Fix up for a now empty focused inline element, e.g. <span contenteditable='true'>Hello</span> became
1002 // <span contenteditable='true'></span>. Hit testing will likely not find this element because the engine
1003 // tries to avoid creating line boxes, which are things it hit tests, for them to reduce memory. If the
1004 // focused element is inside the search rect it's the most likely target for future editing operations,
1005 // even if it's empty. So, we special case it here.
1006 if (auto* focusedElement = focusController().focusedOrMainFrame().document()->focusedElement()) {
1007 if (searchRectInRootViewCoordinates.inclusivelyIntersects(focusedElement->clientRect())) {
1008 if (auto* editableElement = rootEditableElement(*focusedElement))
1009 rootEditableElements.add(*editableElement);
1010 }
1011 }
1012 return WTF::map(rootEditableElements, [](const auto& element) { return element.copyRef(); });
1013}

1017 return focusController().focusedOrMainFrame().selection().selection();

1020void Page::setDefersLoading(bool defers)
1021{
1022 if (!m_settings->loadDeferringEnabled())
1023 return;
1024
1025 if (m_settings->wantsBalancedSetDefersLoadingBehavior()) {
1026 ASSERT(defers || m_defersLoadingCallCount);
1027 if (defers && ++m_defersLoadingCallCount > 1)
1028 return;
1029 if (!defers && --m_defersLoadingCallCount)
1030 return;
1031 } else {
1032 ASSERT(!m_defersLoadingCallCount);
1033 if (defers == m_defersLoading)
1034 return;
1035 }
1036
1037 m_defersLoading = defers;
1038 for (Frame* frame = &mainFrame(); frame; frame = frame->tree().traverseNext())
1039 frame->loader().setDefersLoading(defers);
1040}

1099void Page::setPageScaleFactor(float scale, const IntPoint& origin, bool inStableState)
1100{
1101 LOG(Viewports, "Page::setPageScaleFactor %.2f - inStableState %d", scale, inStableState);
1102
1103 Document* document = mainFrame().document();
1104 RefPtr<FrameView> view = document->view();
1105
1106 if (scale == m_pageScaleFactor) {
1107 if (view && view->scrollPosition() != origin && !delegatesScaling())
1108 document->updateLayoutIgnorePendingStylesheets();
1109 } else {
1110 m_pageScaleFactor = scale;
1111
1112 if (view && !delegatesScaling()) {
1113 view->setNeedsLayoutAfterViewConfigurationChange();
1114 view->setNeedsCompositingGeometryUpdate();
1115
1116 document->resolveStyle(Document::ResolveStyleType::Rebuild);
1117
1118 // Transform change on RenderView doesn't trigger repaint on non-composited contents.
1119 mainFrame().view()->invalidateRect(IntRect(LayoutRect::infiniteRect()));
1120 }
1121
1122 mainFrame().deviceOrPageScaleFactorChanged();
1123
1124 if (view && view->fixedElementsLayoutRelativeToFrame())
1125 view->setViewportConstrainedObjectsNeedLayout();
1126
1127 if (view && view->scrollPosition() != origin && !delegatesScaling() && document->renderView() && document->renderView()->needsLayout() && view->didFirstLayout())
1128 view->layoutContext().layout();
1129 }
1130
1131 if (view && view->scrollPosition() != origin) {
1132 if (!view->delegatesScrolling())
1133 view->setScrollPosition(origin);
1134#if USE(COORDINATED_GRAPHICS)
1135 else
1136 view->requestScrollPositionUpdate(origin);
1137#endif
1138 }
1139
1140#if ENABLE(VIDEO)
1141 if (inStableState) {
1142 forEachMediaElement([] (HTMLMediaElement& element) {
1143 element.pageScaleFactorChanged();
1144 });
1145 }
1146#else
1147 UNUSED_PARAM(inStableState);
1148#endif
1149}

1195void Page::windowScreenDidChange(PlatformDisplayID displayID, std::optional<FramesPerSecond> nominalFramesPerSecond)
1196{
1197 if (displayID == m_displayID && nominalFramesPerSecond == m_displayNominalFramesPerSecond)
1198 return;
1199
1200 m_displayID = displayID;
1201 m_displayNominalFramesPerSecond = nominalFramesPerSecond;
1202 if (!m_displayNominalFramesPerSecond) {
1203 // If the caller didn't give us a refresh rate, maybe the relevant DisplayRefreshMonitor can? This happens in WebKitLegacy
1204 // because WebView doesn't have a convenient way to access the display refresh rate.

1217 });
1218#endif
1219
1220 if (m_scrollingCoordinator)
1221 m_scrollingCoordinator->windowScreenDidChange(displayID, m_displayNominalFramesPerSecond);
1222
1223 renderingUpdateScheduler().windowScreenDidChange(displayID);
1224
1225 setNeedsRecalcStyleInAllFrames();
1226}

1471void Page::computeUnfulfilledRenderingSteps(OptionSet<RenderingUpdateStep> requestedSteps)

1496
1497// https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/webappapis.html#update-the-rendering
1498void Page::updateRendering()
1499{
1500 LOG(EventLoop, "Page %p updateRendering() - re-entering %d", this, !m_renderingUpdateRemainingSteps.isEmpty());
1501
1502 if (m_renderingUpdateRemainingSteps.isEmpty())
1503 m_unfulfilledRequestedSteps = { };
1504
1505 m_renderingUpdateRemainingSteps.append(allRenderingUpdateSteps);
1506
1507 // This function is not reentrant, e.g. a rAF callback may trigger a forces repaint in testing.
1508 // This is why we track m_renderingUpdateRemainingSteps as a stack.
1509 if (m_renderingUpdateRemainingSteps.size() > 1) {
1510 layoutIfNeeded();
1511 m_renderingUpdateRemainingSteps.last().remove(updateRenderingSteps);
1512 return;
1513 }
1514
1515 m_lastRenderingUpdateTimestamp = MonotonicTime::now();
1516
1517 bool isSVGImagePage = chrome().client().isSVGImageChromeClient();
1518 if (!isSVGImagePage)
1519 tracePoint(RenderingUpdateStart);
1520
1521 layoutIfNeeded();
1522
1523#if ENABLE(ASYNC_SCROLLING)
1524 if (auto* scrollingCoordinator = this->scrollingCoordinator())
1525 scrollingCoordinator->willStartRenderingUpdate();
1526#endif
1527
1528 // Timestamps should not change while serving the rendering update steps.
1529 Vector<WeakPtr<Document>> initialDocuments;
1530 forEachDocument([&initialDocuments] (Document& document) {
1531 document.domWindow()->freezeNowTimestamp();
1532 initialDocuments.append(makeWeakPtr(&document));
1533 });
1534
1535 auto runProcessingStep = [&](RenderingUpdateStep step, const WTF::Function<void(Document&)>& perDocumentFunction) {
1536 m_renderingUpdateRemainingSteps.last().remove(step);
1537 forEachDocument(perDocumentFunction);
1538 };
1539
1540 // FIXME: Flush autofocus candidates.
1541
1542 runProcessingStep(RenderingUpdateStep::Resize, [] (Document& document) {
1543 document.runResizeSteps();
1544 });
1545
1546 runProcessingStep(RenderingUpdateStep::Scroll, [] (Document& document) {
1547 document.runScrollSteps();
1548 });
1549
1550 runProcessingStep(RenderingUpdateStep::MediaQueryEvaluation, [] (Document& document) {
1551 document.evaluateMediaQueriesAndReportChanges();
1552 });
1553
1554 runProcessingStep(RenderingUpdateStep::Animations, [] (Document& document) {
1555 document.updateAnimationsAndSendEvents();
1556 });
1557
1558 // FIXME: Run the fullscreen steps.
1559 m_renderingUpdateRemainingSteps.last().remove(RenderingUpdateStep::Fullscreen);
1560
1561 runProcessingStep(RenderingUpdateStep::AnimationFrameCallbacks, [] (Document& document) {
1562 document.serviceRequestAnimationFrameCallbacks();
1563 });
1564
1565 layoutIfNeeded();
1566
1567#if ENABLE(INTERSECTION_OBSERVER)
1568 runProcessingStep(RenderingUpdateStep::IntersectionObservations, [] (Document& document) {
1569 document.updateIntersectionObservations();
1570 });
1571#endif
1572
1573#if ENABLE(RESIZE_OBSERVER)
1574 runProcessingStep(RenderingUpdateStep::ResizeObservations, [&] (Document& document) {
1575 document.updateResizeObservations(*this);
1576 });
1577#endif
1578
1579 runProcessingStep(RenderingUpdateStep::Images, [] (Document& document) {
1580 for (auto& image : document.cachedResourceLoader().allCachedSVGImages()) {
1581 if (auto* page = image->internalPage())
1582 page->isolatedUpdateRendering();
1583 }
1584 });
1585
1586 for (auto& document : initialDocuments) {
1587 if (document && document->domWindow())
1588 document->domWindow()->unfreezeNowTimestamp();
1589 }
1590
1591 m_renderingUpdateRemainingSteps.last().remove(RenderingUpdateStep::WheelEventMonitorCallbacks);
1592
1593 if (UNLIKELY(isMonitoringWheelEvents()))
1594 wheelEventTestMonitor()->checkShouldFireCallbacks();
1595
1596 if (m_isTrackingRenderingUpdates)
1597 ++m_renderingUpdateCount;
1598
1599 layoutIfNeeded();
1600 doAfterUpdateRendering();
1601
1602 if (!isSVGImagePage)
1603 tracePoint(RenderingUpdateEnd);
1604}
1605
1606void Page::isolatedUpdateRendering()
1607{
1608 LOG(EventLoop, "Page %p isolatedUpdateRendering()", this);
1609 updateRendering();
1610 renderingUpdateCompleted();
1611}
1612
1613void Page::doAfterUpdateRendering()
1614{
1615 // Code here should do once-per-frame work that needs to be done before painting, and requires
1616 // layout to be up-to-date. It should not run script, trigger layout, or dirty layout.
1617
1618#if ENABLE(LAYOUT_FORMATTING_CONTEXT)
1619 if (RuntimeEnabledFeatures::sharedFeatures().layoutFormattingContextEnabled()) {
1620 forEachDocument([] (Document& document) {
1621 if (auto* frameView = document.view())
1622 frameView->displayView().prepareForDisplay();
1623 });
1624 }
1625#endif
1626
1627 auto runProcessingStep = [&](RenderingUpdateStep step, const WTF::Function<void(Document&)>& perDocumentFunction) {
1628 m_renderingUpdateRemainingSteps.last().remove(step);
1629 forEachDocument(perDocumentFunction);
1630 };
1631
1632 runProcessingStep(RenderingUpdateStep::CursorUpdate, [] (Document& document) {
1633 if (auto* frame = document.frame())
1634 frame->eventHandler().updateCursorIfNeeded();
1635 });
1636
1637 forEachDocument([] (Document& document) {
1638 document.enqueuePaintTimingEntryIfNeeded();
1639 });
1640
1641 forEachDocument([] (Document& document) {
1642 document.updateHighlightPositions();
1643 });
1644#if ENABLE(APP_HIGHLIGHTS)
1645 forEachDocument([] (Document& document) {
1646 auto appHighlightStorage = document.appHighlightStorageIfExists();
1647 if (!appHighlightStorage)
1648 return;
1649
1650 if (appHighlightStorage->hasUnrestoredHighlights() && MonotonicTime::now() - appHighlightStorage->lastRangeSearchTime() > 1_s) {
1651 appHighlightStorage->resetLastRangeSearchTime();
1652 document.eventLoop().queueTask(TaskSource::InternalAsyncTask, [weakDocument = makeWeakPtr(document)] {
1653 auto document = makeRefPtr(weakDocument.get());
1654 if (!document)
1655 return;
1656
1657 if (auto* appHighlightStorage = document->appHighlightStorageIfExists())
1658 appHighlightStorage->restoreUnrestoredAppHighlights();
1659 });
1660 }
1661 });
1662#endif
1663
1664#if ENABLE(VIDEO)
1665 forEachDocument([] (Document& document) {
1666 document.updateTextTrackRepresentationImageIfNeeded();
1667 });
1668#endif
1669
1670#if ENABLE(IMAGE_ANALYSIS)
1671 updateElementsWithTextRecognitionResults();
1672#endif
1673
1674 prioritizeVisibleResources();
1675
1676 m_renderingUpdateRemainingSteps.last().remove(RenderingUpdateStep::EventRegionUpdate);
1677
1678#if ENABLE(IOS_TOUCH_EVENTS)
1679 // updateTouchEventRegions() needs to be called only on the top document.
1680 if (RefPtr<Document> document = mainFrame().document())
1681 document->updateTouchEventRegions();
1682#endif
1683 forEachDocument([] (Document& document) {
1684 document.updateEventRegions();
1685 });
1686
1687 DebugPageOverlays::doAfterUpdateRendering(*this);
1688
1689 forEachDocument([] (Document& document) {
1690 document.prepareCanvasesForDisplayIfNeeded();
1691 });
1692
1693 ASSERT(!mainFrame().view() || !mainFrame().view()->needsLayout());
1694#if ASSERT_ENABLED
1695 for (Frame* child = mainFrame().tree().firstRenderedChild(); child; child = child->tree().traverseNextRendered()) {
1696 auto* frameView = child->view();
1697 ASSERT(!frameView || !frameView->needsLayout());
1698 }
1699#endif
1700
1701 if (!m_sampledPageTopColor) {
1702 m_sampledPageTopColor = PageColorSampler::sampleTop(*this);
1703 if (m_sampledPageTopColor)
1704 chrome().client().sampledPageTopColorChanged();
1705 }
1706}
1707
1708void Page::finalizeRenderingUpdate(OptionSet<FinalizeRenderingUpdateFlags> flags)
1709{
1710 LOG(EventLoop, "Page %p finalizeRenderingUpdate()", this);
1711
1712 auto* view = mainFrame().view();
1713 if (!view)
1714 return;
1715
1716 if (flags.contains(FinalizeRenderingUpdateFlags::InvalidateImagesWithAsyncDecodes))
1717 view->invalidateImagesWithAsyncDecodes();
1718
1719 m_renderingUpdateRemainingSteps.last().remove(RenderingUpdateStep::LayerFlush);
1720
1721 view->flushCompositingStateIncludingSubframes();
1722
1723#if ENABLE(ASYNC_SCROLLING)
1724 m_renderingUpdateRemainingSteps.last().remove(RenderingUpdateStep::ScrollingTreeUpdate);
1725
1726 if (auto* scrollingCoordinator = this->scrollingCoordinator()) {
1727 scrollingCoordinator->commitTreeStateIfNeeded();
1728 if (flags.contains(FinalizeRenderingUpdateFlags::ApplyScrollingTreeLayerPositions))
1729 scrollingCoordinator->applyScrollingTreeLayerPositions();
1730
1731 scrollingCoordinator->didCompleteRenderingUpdate();
1732 }
1733#endif
1734
1735 ASSERT(m_renderingUpdateRemainingSteps.last().isEmpty());
1736 renderingUpdateCompleted();
1737}
1738
1739void Page::renderingUpdateCompleted()
1740{
1741 m_renderingUpdateRemainingSteps.removeLast();
1742
1743 LOG_WITH_STREAM(EventLoop, stream << "Page " << this << " renderingUpdateCompleted() - steps " << m_renderingUpdateRemainingSteps << " unfulfilled steps " << m_unfulfilledRequestedSteps);
1744
1745 if (m_unfulfilledRequestedSteps) {
1746 scheduleRenderingUpdateInternal();
1747 m_unfulfilledRequestedSteps = { };
1748 }
1749}
1750
1751void Page::prioritizeVisibleResources()
1752{
1753 if (loadSchedulingMode() == LoadSchedulingMode::Direct)
1754 return;
1755 if (!mainFrame().document())
1756 return;
1757
1758 Vector<CachedResource*> toPrioritize;
1759
1760 forEachDocument([&] (Document& document) {
1761 toPrioritize.appendVector(document.cachedResourceLoader().visibleResourcesToPrioritize());
1762 });
1763
1764 auto computeSchedulingMode = [&] {
1765 auto& document = *mainFrame().document();
1766 // Parsing generates resource loads.
1767 if (document.parsing())
1768 return LoadSchedulingMode::Prioritized;
1769
1770 // Async script execution may generate more resource loads that benefit from prioritization.
1771 if (document.scriptRunner().hasPendingScripts())
1772 return LoadSchedulingMode::Prioritized;
1773
1774 // We still haven't finished loading the visible resources.
1775 if (!toPrioritize.isEmpty())
1776 return LoadSchedulingMode::Prioritized;
1777
1778 return LoadSchedulingMode::Direct;
1779 };
1780
1781 setLoadSchedulingMode(computeSchedulingMode());
1782
1783 if (toPrioritize.isEmpty())
1784 return;
1785
1786 auto resourceLoaders = toPrioritize.map([](auto* resource) {
1787 return resource->loader();
1788 });
1789
1790 platformStrategies()->loaderStrategy()->prioritizeResourceLoads(resourceLoaders);
1791}
1792
1793void Page::setLoadSchedulingMode(LoadSchedulingMode mode)
1794{
1795 if (m_loadSchedulingMode == mode)
1796 return;
1797
1798 m_loadSchedulingMode = mode;
1799
1800 platformStrategies()->loaderStrategy()->setResourceLoadSchedulingMode(*this, m_loadSchedulingMode);
1801}

1853
1854void Page::userStyleSheetLocationChanged()
1855{
1856 // FIXME: Eventually we will move to a model of just being handed the sheet
1857 // text instead of loading the URL ourselves.
1858 URL url = m_settings->userStyleSheetLocation();
1859
1860 // Allow any local file URL scheme to be loaded.
1861 if (LegacySchemeRegistry::shouldTreatURLSchemeAsLocal(url.protocol().toStringWithoutCopying()))
1862 m_userStyleSheetPath = url.fileSystemPath();
1863 else
1864 m_userStyleSheetPath = String();
1865
1866 m_didLoadUserStyleSheet = false;
1867 m_userStyleSheet = String();
1868 m_userStyleSheetModificationTime = std::nullopt;
1869
1870 // Data URLs with base64-encoded UTF-8 style sheets are common. We can process them
1871 // synchronously and avoid using a loader.
1872 if (url.protocolIsData() && url.string().startsWith("data:text/css;charset=utf-8;base64,")) {
1873 m_didLoadUserStyleSheet = true;
1874
1875 if (auto styleSheetAsUTF8 = base64Decode(decodeURLEscapeSequences(url.string().substring(35)), Base64DecodeOptions::IgnoreSpacesAndNewLines))
1876 m_userStyleSheet = String::fromUTF8(styleSheetAsUTF8->data(), styleSheetAsUTF8->size());
1877 }
1878
1879 forEachDocument([] (Document& document) {
1880 document.extensionStyleSheets().updatePageUserSheet();
1881 });
1882}
1883
1884const String& Page::userStyleSheet() const
1885{
1886 if (m_userStyleSheetPath.isEmpty())
1887 return m_userStyleSheet;
1888
1889 auto modificationTime = FileSystem::fileModificationTime(m_userStyleSheetPath);
1890 if (!modificationTime) {
1891 // The stylesheet either doesn't exist, was just deleted, or is
1892 // otherwise unreadable. If we've read the stylesheet before, we should
1893 // throw away that data now as it no longer represents what's on disk.
1894 m_userStyleSheet = String();
1895 return m_userStyleSheet;
1896 }
1897
1898 // If the stylesheet hasn't changed since the last time we read it, we can
1899 // just return the old data.
1900 if (m_didLoadUserStyleSheet && (m_userStyleSheetModificationTime && modificationTime.value() <= m_userStyleSheetModificationTime.value()))
1901 return m_userStyleSheet;
1902
1903 m_didLoadUserStyleSheet = true;
1904 m_userStyleSheet = String();
1905 m_userStyleSheetModificationTime = modificationTime;
1906
1907 // FIXME: It would be better to load this asynchronously to avoid blocking
1908 // the process, but we will first need to create an asynchronous loading
1909 // mechanism that is not tied to a particular Frame. We will also have to
1910 // determine what our behavior should be before the stylesheet is loaded
1911 // and what should happen when it finishes loading, especially with respect
1912 // to when the load event fires, when Document::close is called, and when
1913 // layout/paint are allowed to happen.
1914 auto data = SharedBuffer::createWithContentsOfFile(m_userStyleSheetPath);
1915 if (!data)
1916 return m_userStyleSheet;
1917
1918 m_userStyleSheet = TextResourceDecoder::create("text/css")->decodeAndFlush(data->data(), data->size());
1919
1920 return m_userStyleSheet;
1921}

2010void Page::hiddenPageDOMTimerThrottlingStateChanged()

2014 updateTimerThrottlingState();
2015}
2016
2017void Page::updateTimerThrottlingState()
2018{
2019 // Timer throttling disabled if page is visually active, or disabled by setting.
2020 if (!m_settings->hiddenPageDOMTimerThrottlingEnabled() || !(m_activityState & ActivityState::IsVisuallyIdle)) {
2021 setTimerThrottlingState(TimerThrottlingState::Disabled);
2022 return;
2023 }
2024
2025 // If the page is visible (but idle), there is any activity (loading, media playing, etc), or per setting,
2026 // we allow timer throttling, but not increasing timer throttling.
2027 if (!m_settings->hiddenPageDOMTimerThrottlingAutoIncreases()
2028 || m_activityState.containsAny({ActivityState::IsVisible, ActivityState::IsAudible, ActivityState::IsLoading, ActivityState::IsCapturingMedia })) {
2029 setTimerThrottlingState(TimerThrottlingState::Enabled);
2030 return;
2031 }
2032
2033 // If we get here increasing timer throttling is enabled.
2034 setTimerThrottlingState(TimerThrottlingState::EnabledIncreasing);
2035}
2036
2037void Page::setTimerThrottlingState(TimerThrottlingState state)
2038{
2039 if (state == m_timerThrottlingState)
2040 return;
2041
2042 m_timerThrottlingState = state;
2043 m_timerThrottlingStateLastChangedTime = MonotonicTime::now();
2044
2045 updateDOMTimerAlignmentInterval();
2046
2047 // When throttling is disabled, release all throttled timers.
2048 if (state == TimerThrottlingState::Disabled) {
2049 forEachDocument([] (Document& document) {
2050 document.didChangeTimerAlignmentInterval();
2051 });
2052 }
2053}
2054
2055void Page::setDOMTimerAlignmentIntervalIncreaseLimit(Seconds limit)
2056{
2057 m_domTimerAlignmentIntervalIncreaseLimit = limit;
2058
2059 // If (m_domTimerAlignmentIntervalIncreaseLimit < m_domTimerAlignmentInterval) then we need
2060 // to update m_domTimerAlignmentInterval, if greater then need to restart the increase timer.
2061 if (m_timerThrottlingState == TimerThrottlingState::EnabledIncreasing)
2062 updateDOMTimerAlignmentInterval();
2063}
2064
2065void Page::updateDOMTimerAlignmentInterval()
2066{
2067 bool needsIncreaseTimer = false;
2068
2069 switch (m_timerThrottlingState) {
2070 case TimerThrottlingState::Disabled:
2071 m_domTimerAlignmentInterval = isLowPowerModeEnabled() ? DOMTimer::defaultAlignmentIntervalInLowPowerMode() : DOMTimer::defaultAlignmentInterval();
2072 break;
2073
2074 case TimerThrottlingState::Enabled:
2075 m_domTimerAlignmentInterval = DOMTimer::hiddenPageAlignmentInterval();
2076 break;
2077
2078 case TimerThrottlingState::EnabledIncreasing:
2079 // For pages in prerender state maximum throttling kicks in immediately.
2080 if (m_isPrerender)
2081 m_domTimerAlignmentInterval = m_domTimerAlignmentIntervalIncreaseLimit;
2082 else {
2083 ASSERT(!!m_timerThrottlingStateLastChangedTime);
2084 m_domTimerAlignmentInterval = MonotonicTime::now() - m_timerThrottlingStateLastChangedTime;
2085 // If we're below the limit, set the timer. If above, clamp to limit.
2086 if (m_domTimerAlignmentInterval < m_domTimerAlignmentIntervalIncreaseLimit)
2087 needsIncreaseTimer = true;
2088 else
2089 m_domTimerAlignmentInterval = m_domTimerAlignmentIntervalIncreaseLimit;
2090 }
2091 // Alignment interval should not be less than DOMTimer::hiddenPageAlignmentInterval().
2092 m_domTimerAlignmentInterval = std::max(m_domTimerAlignmentInterval, DOMTimer::hiddenPageAlignmentInterval());
2093 }
2094
2095 // If throttling is enabled, auto-increasing of throttling is enabled, and the auto-increase
2096 // limit has not yet been reached, and then arm the timer to consider an increase. Time to wait
2097 // between increases is equal to the current throttle time. Since alinment interval increases
2098 // exponentially, time between steps is exponential too.
2099 if (!needsIncreaseTimer)
2100 m_domTimerAlignmentIntervalIncreaseTimer.stop();
2101 else if (!m_domTimerAlignmentIntervalIncreaseTimer.isActive())
2102 m_domTimerAlignmentIntervalIncreaseTimer.startOneShot(m_domTimerAlignmentInterval);
2103}
2104
2105void Page::domTimerAlignmentIntervalIncreaseTimerFired()
2106{
2107 ASSERT(m_settings->hiddenPageDOMTimerThrottlingAutoIncreases());
2108 ASSERT(m_timerThrottlingState == TimerThrottlingState::EnabledIncreasing);
2109 ASSERT(m_domTimerAlignmentInterval < m_domTimerAlignmentIntervalIncreaseLimit);
2110
2111 // Alignment interval is increased to equal the time the page has been throttled, to a limit.
2112 updateDOMTimerAlignmentInterval();
2113}

2312void Page::setActivityState(OptionSet<ActivityState::Flag> activityState)
2313{
2314 auto changed = m_activityState ^ activityState;
2315 if (!changed)
2316 return;
2317
2318 auto oldActivityState = m_activityState;
2319
2320 bool wasVisibleAndActive = isVisibleAndActive();
2321 m_activityState = activityState;
2322
2323 m_focusController->setActivityState(activityState);
2324
2325 if (changed & ActivityState::IsVisible)
2326 setIsVisibleInternal(activityState.contains(ActivityState::IsVisible));

2613// These are magical constants that might be tweaked over time.
2614static const double gMinimumPaintedAreaRatio = 0.1;
2615static const double gMaximumUnpaintedAreaRatio = 0.04;
2616
2617bool Page::isCountingRelevantRepaintedObjects() const
2618{
2619 return m_isCountingRelevantRepaintedObjects && m_requestedLayoutMilestones.contains(DidHitRelevantRepaintedObjectsAreaThreshold);
2620}

2622void Page::startCountingRelevantRepaintedObjects()
2623{
2624 // Reset everything in case we didn't hit the threshold last time.
2625 resetRelevantPaintedObjectCounter();
2626

2628}
2629
2630void Page::resetRelevantPaintedObjectCounter()
2631{
2632 m_isCountingRelevantRepaintedObjects = false;
2633 m_relevantUnpaintedRenderObjects.clear();
2634 m_topRelevantPaintedRegion = Region();
2635 m_bottomRelevantPaintedRegion = Region();
2636 m_relevantUnpaintedRegion = Region();
2637}
2638
2639static LayoutRect relevantViewRect(RenderView* view)
2640{
2641 LayoutRect viewRect = view->viewRect();
2642
2643 float relevantViewRectWidth = 980;
2644#if PLATFORM(WATCHOS)
2645 // FIXME(186051): Consider limiting the relevant rect width to the view width everywhere.
2646 relevantViewRectWidth = std::min<float>(viewRect.width().toFloat(), relevantViewRectWidth);
2647#endif
2648
2649 // DidHitRelevantRepaintedObjectsAreaThreshold is a LayoutMilestone intended to indicate that
2650 // a certain relevant amount of content has been drawn to the screen. This is the rect that
2651 // has been determined to be relevant in the context of this goal. We may choose to tweak
2652 // the rect over time, much like we may choose to tweak gMinimumPaintedAreaRatio and
2653 // gMaximumUnpaintedAreaRatio. But this seems to work well right now.
2654 LayoutRect relevantViewRect { 0, 0, LayoutUnit(relevantViewRectWidth), 1300 };
2655 // If the viewRect is wider than the relevantViewRect, center the relevantViewRect.
2656 if (viewRect.width() > relevantViewRect.width())
2657 relevantViewRect.setX((viewRect.width() - relevantViewRect.width()) / 2);
2658
2659 return relevantViewRect;
2660}
2661
2662void Page::addRelevantRepaintedObject(RenderObject* object, const LayoutRect& objectPaintRect)
2663{
2664 if (!isCountingRelevantRepaintedObjects())
2665 return;
2666
2667 // Objects inside sub-frames are not considered to be relevant.
2668 if (&object->frame() != &mainFrame())
2669 return;
2670
2671 LayoutRect relevantRect = relevantViewRect(&object->view());
2672
2673 // The objects are only relevant if they are being painted within the viewRect().
2674 if (!objectPaintRect.intersects(snappedIntRect(relevantRect)))
2675 return;
2676
2677 IntRect snappedPaintRect = snappedIntRect(objectPaintRect);
2678
2679 // If this object was previously counted as an unpainted object, remove it from that HashSet
2680 // and corresponding Region. FIXME: This doesn't do the right thing if the objects overlap.
2681 if (m_relevantUnpaintedRenderObjects.remove(object))
2682 m_relevantUnpaintedRegion.subtract(snappedPaintRect);
2683
2684 // Split the relevantRect into a top half and a bottom half. Making sure we have coverage in
2685 // both halves helps to prevent cases where we have a fully loaded menu bar or masthead with
2686 // no content beneath that.
2687 LayoutRect topRelevantRect = relevantRect;
2688 topRelevantRect.contract(LayoutSize(0_lu, relevantRect.height() / 2));
2689 LayoutRect bottomRelevantRect = topRelevantRect;
2690 bottomRelevantRect.setY(relevantRect.height() / 2);
2691
2692 // If the rect straddles both Regions, split it appropriately.
2693 if (topRelevantRect.intersects(snappedPaintRect) && bottomRelevantRect.intersects(snappedPaintRect)) {
2694 IntRect topIntersection = snappedPaintRect;
2695 topIntersection.intersect(snappedIntRect(topRelevantRect));
2696 m_topRelevantPaintedRegion.unite(topIntersection);
2697
2698 IntRect bottomIntersection = snappedPaintRect;
2699 bottomIntersection.intersect(snappedIntRect(bottomRelevantRect));
2700 m_bottomRelevantPaintedRegion.unite(bottomIntersection);
2701 } else if (topRelevantRect.intersects(snappedPaintRect))
2702 m_topRelevantPaintedRegion.unite(snappedPaintRect);
2703 else
2704 m_bottomRelevantPaintedRegion.unite(snappedPaintRect);
2705
2706 float topPaintedArea = m_topRelevantPaintedRegion.totalArea();
2707 float bottomPaintedArea = m_bottomRelevantPaintedRegion.totalArea();
2708 float viewArea = relevantRect.width() * relevantRect.height();
2709
2710 float ratioThatIsPaintedOnTop = topPaintedArea / viewArea;
2711 float ratioThatIsPaintedOnBottom = bottomPaintedArea / viewArea;
2712 float ratioOfViewThatIsUnpainted = m_relevantUnpaintedRegion.totalArea() / viewArea;
2713
2714 if (ratioThatIsPaintedOnTop > (gMinimumPaintedAreaRatio / 2) && ratioThatIsPaintedOnBottom > (gMinimumPaintedAreaRatio / 2)
2715 && ratioOfViewThatIsUnpainted < gMaximumUnpaintedAreaRatio) {
2716 m_isCountingRelevantRepaintedObjects = false;
2717 resetRelevantPaintedObjectCounter();
2718 if (Frame* frame = &mainFrame())
2719 frame->loader().didReachLayoutMilestone(DidHitRelevantRepaintedObjectsAreaThreshold);
2720 }
2721}
2722
2723void Page::addRelevantUnpaintedObject(RenderObject* object, const LayoutRect& objectPaintRect)
2724{
2725 if (!isCountingRelevantRepaintedObjects())
2726 return;
2727
2728 // The objects are only relevant if they are being painted within the relevantViewRect().
2729 if (!objectPaintRect.intersects(snappedIntRect(relevantViewRect(&object->view()))))
2730 return;
2731
2732 m_relevantUnpaintedRenderObjects.add(object);
2733 m_relevantUnpaintedRegion.unite(snappedIntRect(objectPaintRect));
2734}

2847void Page::logNavigation(const Navigation& navigation)
2848{
2849 String navigationDescription;
2850 switch (navigation.type) {
2851 case FrameLoadType::Standard:
2852 navigationDescription = "standard"_s;
2853 break;
2854 case FrameLoadType::Back:
2855 navigationDescription = "back"_s;
2856 break;
2857 case FrameLoadType::Forward:
2858 navigationDescription = "forward"_s;
2859 break;
2860 case FrameLoadType::IndexedBackForward:
2861 navigationDescription = "indexedBackForward"_s;
2862 break;
2863 case FrameLoadType::Reload:
2864 navigationDescription = "reload"_s;
2865 break;
2866 case FrameLoadType::Same:
2867 navigationDescription = "same"_s;
2868 break;
2869 case FrameLoadType::ReloadFromOrigin:
2870 navigationDescription = "reloadFromOrigin"_s;
2871 break;
2872 case FrameLoadType::ReloadExpiredOnly:
2873 navigationDescription = "reloadRevalidatingExpired"_s;
2874 break;
2875 case FrameLoadType::Replace:
2876 case FrameLoadType::RedirectWithLockedBackForwardList:
2877 // Not logging those for now.
2878 return;
2879 }
2880 diagnosticLoggingClient().logDiagnosticMessage(DiagnosticLoggingKeys::navigationKey(), navigationDescription, ShouldSample::No);
2881
2882 if (!navigation.domain.isEmpty())
2883 diagnosticLoggingClient().logDiagnosticMessageWithEnhancedPrivacy(DiagnosticLoggingKeys::domainVisitedKey(), navigation.domain.string(), ShouldSample::Yes);
2884}
2885
2886void Page::mainFrameLoadStarted(const URL& destinationURL, FrameLoadType type)
2887{
2888 Navigation navigation = { RegistrableDomain { destinationURL }, type };
2889
2890 // To avoid being too verbose, we only log navigations if the page is or becomes visible. This avoids logging non-user observable loads.
2891 if (!isVisible()) {
2892 m_navigationToLogWhenVisible = navigation;
2893 return;
2894 }
2895
2896 m_navigationToLogWhenVisible = std::nullopt;
2897 logNavigation(navigation);
2898}

2947void Page::setSessionID(PAL::SessionID sessionID)
2948{
2949 ASSERT(sessionID.isValid());
2950 ASSERT(m_sessionID == PAL::SessionID::legacyPrivateSessionID() || m_sessionID == PAL::SessionID::defaultSessionID());
2951 ASSERT(sessionID == PAL::SessionID::legacyPrivateSessionID() || sessionID == PAL::SessionID::defaultSessionID());
2952
2953 if (sessionID != m_sessionID)
2954 m_idbConnectionToServer = nullptr;
2955
2956 if (sessionID != m_sessionID && m_sessionStorage)
2957 m_sessionStorage->setSessionIDForTesting(sessionID);
2958
2959 bool privateBrowsingStateChanged = (sessionID.isEphemeral() != m_sessionID.isEphemeral());
2960
2961 m_sessionID = sessionID;
2962
2963 if (!privateBrowsingStateChanged)
2964 return;
2965

2967 document.privateBrowsingStateDidChange(m_sessionID);
2968 });
2969
2970 // Collect the PluginViews in to a vector to ensure that action the plug-in takes
2971 // from below privateBrowsingStateChanged does not affect their lifetime.
2972
2973 for (auto& view : pluginViews())
2974 view->privateBrowsingStateChanged(sessionID.isEphemeral());

3524
3525void Page::injectUserStyleSheet(UserStyleSheet& userStyleSheet)
3526{
3527#if ENABLE(APP_BOUND_DOMAINS)
3528 if (m_mainFrame->loader().client().shouldEnableInAppBrowserPrivacyProtections()) {
3529 if (auto* document = m_mainFrame->document())
3530 document->addConsoleMessage(MessageSource::Security, MessageLevel::Warning, "Ignoring user style sheet for non-app bound domain."_s);
3531 return;
3532 }
3533 m_mainFrame->loader().client().notifyPageOfAppBoundBehavior();
3534#endif
3535
3536 // We need to wait until we're no longer displaying the initial empty document before we can inject the stylesheets.
3537 if (m_mainFrame->loader().stateMachine().isDisplayingInitialEmptyDocument()) {
3538 m_userStyleSheetsPendingInjection.append(userStyleSheet);
3539 return;
3540 }
3541
3542 if (userStyleSheet.injectedFrames() == UserContentInjectedFrames::InjectInTopFrameOnly) {
3543 if (auto* document = m_mainFrame->document())
3544 document->extensionStyleSheets().injectPageSpecificUserStyleSheet(userStyleSheet);
3545 } else {
3546 forEachDocument([&] (Document& document) {
3547 document.extensionStyleSheets().injectPageSpecificUserStyleSheet(userStyleSheet);
3548 });
3549 }

3563 document->extensionStyleSheets().removePageSpecificUserStyleSheet(userStyleSheet);

3613void Page::updateElementsWithTextRecognitionResults()
3614{
3615 if (m_textRecognitionResultsByElement.isEmpty())
3616 return;
3617
3618 m_textRecognitionResultsByElement.removeAllMatching([](auto& elementAndResult) {
3619 return !elementAndResult.first;
3620 });
3621
3622 Vector<std::pair<Ref<HTMLElement>, TextRecognitionResult>> elementsToUpdate;
3623 for (auto& [element, resultAndRect] : m_textRecognitionResultsByElement) {
3624 if (!element->isConnected())
3625 continue;
3626
3627 auto& [result, containerRect] = resultAndRect;
3628 auto protectedElement = makeRef(*element);
3629 auto renderer = protectedElement->renderer();
3630 if (!is<RenderImage>(renderer))
3631 continue;
3632
3633 auto newContainerRect = enclosingIntRect(downcast<RenderImage>(*renderer).replacedContentRect());
3634 if (containerRect == newContainerRect)
3635 continue;
3636
3637 containerRect = newContainerRect;
3638 elementsToUpdate.append({ WTFMove(protectedElement), result });
3639 }
3640
3641 for (auto& [element, result] : elementsToUpdate) {
3642 element->document().eventLoop().queueTask(TaskSource::InternalAsyncTask, [result = TextRecognitionResult { result }, weakElement = makeWeakPtr(element.get())] {
3643 auto element = makeRefPtr(weakElement.get());
3644 if (!element)
3645 return;
3646
3647 element->updateWithTextRecognitionResult(result, HTMLElement::CacheTextRecognitionResults::No);
3648 });
3649 }
3650}

3652bool Page::hasCachedTextRecognitionResult(const HTMLElement& element) const
3653{
3654 return m_elementsWithTextRecognitionResults.contains(element);
3655}
3656
3657void Page::cacheTextRecognitionResult(const HTMLElement& element, const IntRect& containerRect, const TextRecognitionResult& result)
3658{
3659 m_elementsWithTextRecognitionResults.add(element);
3660
3661 auto index = m_textRecognitionResultsByElement.findMatching([&](auto& elementAndResult) {
3662 return elementAndResult.first == &element;
3663 });
3664
3665 if (index == notFound)
3666 m_textRecognitionResultsByElement.append({ makeWeakPtr(element), { result, containerRect } });
3667 else
3668 m_textRecognitionResultsByElement[index].second = { result, containerRect };
3669
3670 m_textRecognitionResultsByElement.removeAllMatching([](auto& elementAndResult) {
3671 return !elementAndResult.first;
3672 });
3673}
